FBIS4-5951 "dreas073_d_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 South Korea DPRK To `Accede' to Talks If U.S. Proposal DPRK To `Accede' to Talks If U.S. Proposal SK1404224194 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2209 GMT 14 Apr 94 SK1404224194 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Korean BFN [YONHAP from United Nations] [Text] Kim Chong-su, deputy chief of the North Korean mission in the United Nations, stated on 14 April that if the United States proposes holding the third round of U.S.-North Korean high-level talks, North Korea will accede to [unghagettago] it. Expressing the strong desire for the resumption of U.S.-North Korean high-level talks, Kim said that the United States should arrange the resumption of talks since the United States unilaterally [ilbangjoguro] canceled the third round of high-level talks. He insisted that the additional nuclear inspection issue should be discussed at the third round of talks and that the South-North exchange of special envoys should not be linked to U.S.-North Korean talks because it is a national issue [minjokkanui munje].
